<br>
Everyone in the town seems to respond to 'Who is Seru/Katta?' the same, but certain people respond differently to '<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> What</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is Seru/Katta?'.  I'm specifically speaking about the Praeserti in Seru.  You can also ask the different Praeserti about each other which yields some humorous things. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uskecpataintedblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skecpa Taintedblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/23/01 6:59:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3597.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sanctus Seru factions</span><hr size=1> The Praesertum respond differently to &quot;Who is Seru&quot; and &quot;Who Seru&quot; differently. Without the Is they give generic response <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utyknee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tyknee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/23/01 9:17:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3597.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sanctus Seru factions</span><hr size=1> I posted this in a back alley thread, but I wanted to repost it here.<br>
<br>
I've found that the names of the mobs are VERY misleading as to what faction they are on, so do NOT trust the mob name. For example, the mobs in Marus Seru, named &quot;A Hand of Seru&quot; which con dubious to me, appear to be on Hand Legionaires faction (first hit on the list when killed). The mobs in Dawnshroud Peak, which I believed are named &quot;Legionaire XXX&quot; I'm going to assume are on the same faction (will kill one to verify). However the mobs inside Sanctus Seru, also named &quot;Legionaire XXX&quot; appear to be on Hand of Seru faction (again first hit when killed).<br>
<br>
So, apply a little logic (which isn't 100% foolproof either), it would appear that the faction needed to clear the first set of guards is &quot;Hand of Seru&quot;. This faction can be raised by either killing Recursos in Marus Sactu (very green at 60, druid and paladin class mobs) or by killing Spire Sprites in Mons Letalis (a bit harder, some are light blue, Necros, and the zone is much more dangerous, however you get Citizen's faction with these and not with the recursos).  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13>Quests of Norrath</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
